### Define Next.js App Router Root Layout

Source: https://github.com/vercel/next.js/blob/canary/docs/01-app/01-getting-started/01-installation.mdx

This snippet demonstrates how to create the mandatory `RootLayout` component for the Next.js App Router. It defines the basic HTML structure for the entire application, including `<html>` and `<body>` tags, and renders child components within the body. This layout is applied globally to all routes in the `app` directory.

```tsx
export default function RootLayout({
  children,
}: {
  children: React.ReactNode
}) {
  return (
    <html lang="en">
      <body>{children}</body>
    </html>
  )
}
```

