### Load a Global Script for All Routes (App Router)

Source: https://github.com/vercel/next.js/blob/canary/docs/01-app/02-guides/scripts.mdx

To load a third-party script for all routes in an application using the App Router, import `next/script` and include it in the root layout. This script will load and execute when any route in your application is accessed, but only once.

```tsx
import Script from 'next/script'

export default function RootLayout({
  children,
}: {
  children: React.ReactNode
}) {
  return (
    <html lang="en">
      <body>{children}</body>
      <Script src="https://example.com/script.js" />
    </html>
  )
}
```

